# Analysis of Competing Hypotheses (ACH) Matrix Builder

Structuring competing theories prevents confirmation bias. Analysts frequently fall in love with their first conclusion. Applying the ACH method forces rigorous evidence testing. Feed the following prompt and JSON structure to the LLM to generate a foundational matrix.

***

**SYSTEM INSTRUCTION: ACH MATRIX GENERATION**

You are a strategic intelligence engine. I will provide a list of evidence and three competing hypotheses regarding a geopolitical event. Construct an ACH matrix. 

Evaluate every piece of evidence against every hypothesis. Score the evidence as Consistent (C), Inconsistent (I), or Not Applicable (NA). 

Output a JSON structure matching the exact format below. Calculate the inconsistency score for each hypothesis. Hypotheses with the highest inconsistency scores hold the lowest probability of being true.

```json
{
  "ach_matrix": {
    "evidence_item_1": {
      "source_ranking": "High Confidence",
      "hypothesis_1_eval": "I",
      "hypothesis_2_eval": "C",
      "hypothesis_3_eval": "C"
    }
  }
}
